24// Marks are used during traversal of the graph to distinguish states of nodes.
25// Each node has a mark which is a monotonically increasing integer, and a
26// {NodeMarker} has a range of values that indicate states of a node.
27using Mark = uint32_t;
28
29// NodeIds are identifying numbers for nodes that can be used to index auxiliary
30// out-of-line data associated with each node.
31using NodeId = uint32_t;
32
33// A Node is the basic primitive of graphs. Nodes are chained together by
34// input/use chains but by default otherwise contain only an identifying number
35// which specific applications of graphs and nodes can use to index auxiliary
36// out-of-line data, especially transient data.
37//
38// In addition Nodes only contain a mutable Operator that may change during
39// compilation, e.g. during lowering passes. Other information that needs to be
40// associated with Nodes during compilation must be stored out-of-line indexed
41// by the Node's id.
42class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE Node final {
43 public:
44 static Node* New(Zone* zone, NodeId id, const Operator* op, int input_count,
45 Node* const* inputs, bool has_extensible_inputs);
46 static Node* Clone(Zone* zone, NodeId id, const Node* node);
47
48 inline bool IsDead() const;
49 void Kill();
50
51 const Operator* op() const { return op_; }
52
53 constexpr IrOpcode::Value opcode() const {
54 DCHECK_GE(IrOpcode::kLast, op_->opcode());
55 return static_cast<IrOpcode::Value>(op_->opcode());
56 }
57
58 NodeId id() const { return IdField::decode(bit_field_); }
59
60 int InputCount() const {
61 return has_inline_inputs() ? InlineCountField::decode(bit_field_)
62 : outline_inputs()->count_;
63 }

65#ifdef DEBUG
66 void Verify();
67#else
68 inline void Verify() {}
69#endif

71 Node* InputAt(int index) const {
72 DCHECK_LE(0, index);
73 DCHECK_LT(index, InputCount());
74 return *GetInputPtrConst(index);
75 }
76
77 void ReplaceInput(int index, Node* new_to) {
78 DCHECK_LE(0, index);
79 DCHECK_LT(index, InputCount());
80 ZoneNodePtr* input_ptr = GetInputPtr(index);
81 Node* old_to = *input_ptr;
82 if (old_to != new_to) {
83 Use* use = GetUsePtr(index);
84 if (old_to) old_to->RemoveUse(use);
85 *input_ptr = new_to;
86 if (new_to) new_to->AppendUse(use);
87 }
88 }

166 // Out of line storage for inputs when the number of inputs overflowed the
167 // capacity of the inline-allocated space.
168 struct OutOfLineInputs {
169 ZoneNodePtr node_;
170 int count_;
171 int capacity_;
172
173 // Inputs are allocated right behind the OutOfLineInputs instance.
174 inline ZoneNodePtr* inputs();
175
176 static OutOfLineInputs* New(Zone* zone, int capacity);
177 void ExtractFrom(Use* use_ptr, ZoneNodePtr* input_ptr, int count);
178 };
179 using ZoneOutOfLineInputsPtr = GraphZoneTraits::Ptr<OutOfLineInputs>;
180
181 // A link in the use chain for a node. Every input {i} to a node {n} has an
182 // associated {Use} which is linked into the use chain of the {i} node.
183 struct Use {
184 ZoneUsePtr next;
185 ZoneUsePtr prev;
186 uint32_t bit_field_;
187
188 int input_index() const { return InputIndexField::decode(bit_field_); }
189 bool is_inline_use() const { return InlineField::decode(bit_field_); }
190 ZoneNodePtr* input_ptr() {
191 int index = input_index();
192 Use* start = this + 1 + index;
193 ZoneNodePtr* inputs =
194 is_inline_use() ? reinterpret_cast<Node*>(start)->inline_inputs()
195 : reinterpret_cast<OutOfLineInputs*>(start)->inputs();
196 return &inputs[index];
197 }
198
199 Node* from() {
200 Use* start = this + 1 + input_index();
201 return is_inline_use() ? reinterpret_cast<Node*>(start)
202 : reinterpret_cast<OutOfLineInputs*>(start)->node_;
203 }
204
205 using InlineField = base::BitField<bool, 0, 1>;
206 using InputIndexField = base::BitField<unsigned, 1, 31>;
207 };
208
209 //============================================================================
210 //== Memory layout ===========================================================
211 //============================================================================
212 // Saving space for big graphs is important. We use a memory layout trick to
213 // be able to map {Node} objects to {Use} objects and vice-versa in a
214 // space-efficient manner.
215 //
216 // {Use} links are laid out in memory directly before a {Node}, followed by
217 // direct pointers to input {Nodes}.
218 //
219 // inline case:
220 // |Use #N |Use #N-1|...|Use #1 |Use #0 |Node xxxx |I#0|I#1|...|I#N-1|I#N|
221 // ^ ^ ^
222 // + Use + Node + Input
223 //
224 // Since every {Use} instance records its {input_index}, pointer arithmetic
225 // can compute the {Node}.
226 //
227 // out-of-line case:
228 // |Node xxxx |
229 // ^ + outline ------------------+
230 // +----------------------------------------+
231 // | |
232 // v | node
233 // |Use #N |Use #N-1|...|Use #1 |Use #0 |OOL xxxxx |I#0|I#1|...|I#N-1|I#N|
234 // ^ ^
235 // + Use + Input
236 //
237 // Out-of-line storage of input lists is needed if appending an input to
238 // a node exceeds the maximum inline capacity.
239
240 Node(NodeId id, const Operator* op, int inline_count, int inline_capacity);
241 Node(const Node&) = delete;
242 Node& operator=(const Node&) = delete;
243
244 inline Address inputs_location() const;
245
246 ZoneNodePtr* inline_inputs() const {
247 return reinterpret_cast<ZoneNodePtr*>(inputs_location());
248 }
249 OutOfLineInputs* outline_inputs() const {
250 return *reinterpret_cast<ZoneOutOfLineInputsPtr*>(inputs_location());
251 }
252 void set_outline_inputs(OutOfLineInputs* outline) {
253 *reinterpret_cast<ZoneOutOfLineInputsPtr*>(inputs_location()) = outline;
254 }
255
256 ZoneNodePtr const* GetInputPtrConst(int input_index) const {
257 return has_inline_inputs() ? &(inline_inputs()[input_index])
258 : &(outline_inputs()->inputs()[input_index]);
259 }
260 ZoneNodePtr* GetInputPtr(int input_index) {
261 return has_inline_inputs() ? &(inline_inputs()[input_index])
262 : &(outline_inputs()->inputs()[input_index]);
263 }
264 Use* GetUsePtr(int input_index) {
265 Use* ptr = has_inline_inputs() ? reinterpret_cast<Use*>(this)
266 : reinterpret_cast<Use*>(outline_inputs());
267 return &ptr[-1 - input_index];
268 }

320// Base class for node wrappers.
321class NodeWrapper {
322 public:

324 operator Node*() const { return node_; }
325 Node* operator->() const { return node_; }
326
327 protected:
328 Node* node() const { return node_; }
329 void set_node(Node* node) {
330 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(node);
331 node_ = node;
332 }

334 private:
335 Node* node_;
336};

338// Wrapper classes for special node/edge types (effect, control, frame states).
339
340class Effect : public NodeWrapper {
341 public:
342 explicit constexpr Effect(Node* node) : NodeWrapper(node) {
343 // TODO(jgruber): Remove the End special case.
344 SLOW_DCHECK(node == nullptr || node->op()->opcode() == IrOpcode::kEnd ||
345 node->op()->EffectOutputCount() > 0);
346 }
347
348 // Support the common `Node* x = effect = ...` pattern.
349 Node* operator=(Node* value) {
350 DCHECK_GT(value->op()->EffectOutputCount(), 0);
351 set_node(value);
352 return value;
353 }
354};
355
356class Control : public NodeWrapper {
357 public:
358 explicit constexpr Control(Node* node) : NodeWrapper(node) {
359 // TODO(jgruber): Remove the End special case.
360 SLOW_DCHECK(node == nullptr || node->opcode() == IrOpcode::kEnd ||
361 node->op()->ControlOutputCount() > 0);
362 }
363
364 // Support the common `Node* x = control = ...` pattern.
365 Node* operator=(Node* value) {
366 DCHECK_GT(value->op()->ControlOutputCount(), 0);
367 set_node(value);
368 return value;
369 }
370};

421// An encapsulation for information associated with a single use of node as a
422// input from another node, allowing access to both the defining node and
423// the node having the input.
424class Edge final {
425 public:
426 Node* from() const { return use_->from(); }
427 Node* to() const { return *input_ptr_; }
428 int index() const {
429 int const index = use_->input_index();
430 DCHECK_LT(index, use_->from()->InputCount());
431 return index;
432 }
433
434 bool operator==(const Edge& other) { return input_ptr_ == other.input_ptr_; }
435 bool operator!=(const Edge& other) { return !(*this == other); }
436
437 void UpdateTo(Node* new_to) {
438 Node* old_to = *input_ptr_;
439 if (old_to != new_to) {
440 if (old_to) old_to->RemoveUse(use_);
441 *input_ptr_ = new_to;
442 if (new_to) new_to->AppendUse(use_);
443 }
444 }
445
446 private:
447 friend class Node::UseEdges::iterator;
448 friend class Node::InputEdges;
449 friend class Node::InputEdges::iterator;
450
451 Edge(Node::Use* use, ZoneNodePtr* input_ptr)
452 : use_(use), input_ptr_(input_ptr) {
453 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(use);
454 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(input_ptr);
455 DCHECK_EQ(input_ptr, use->input_ptr());
456 }
457
458 Node::Use* use_;
459 ZoneNodePtr* input_ptr_;
460};

462bool Node::IsDead() const {
463 Node::Inputs inputs = this->inputs();
464 return inputs.count() > 0 && inputs[0] == nullptr;
465}
466
467Node::InputEdges Node::input_edges() {
468 int inline_count = InlineCountField::decode(bit_field_);
469 if (inline_count != kOutlineMarker) {
470 return InputEdges(inline_inputs(), reinterpret_cast<Use*>(this) - 1,
471 inline_count);
472 } else {
473 return InputEdges(outline_inputs()->inputs(),
474 reinterpret_cast<Use*>(outline_inputs()) - 1,
475 outline_inputs()->count_);
476 }
477}
478
479Node::Inputs Node::inputs() const {
480 int inline_count = InlineCountField::decode(bit_field_);
481 if (inline_count != kOutlineMarker) {
482 return Inputs(inline_inputs(), inline_count);
483 } else {
484 return Inputs(outline_inputs()->inputs(), outline_inputs()->count_);
485 }
486}
487
488base::Vector<Node*> Node::inputs_vector() const {
489 int inline_count = InlineCountField::decode(bit_field_);
490 if (inline_count != kOutlineMarker) {
491 return base::VectorOf<Node*>(inline_inputs(), inline_count);
492 } else {
493 return base::VectorOf<Node*>(outline_inputs()->inputs(),
494 outline_inputs()->count_);
495 }
496}

498// A forward iterator to visit the edges for the input dependencies of a node.
499class Node::InputEdges::iterator final {
500 public:
501 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
502 using difference_type = std::ptrdiff_t;
503 using value_type = Edge;
504 using pointer = Edge*;
505 using reference = Edge&;
506
507 iterator() : use_(nullptr), input_ptr_(nullptr) {}
508 iterator(const iterator& other) = default;
509
510 Edge operator*() const { return Edge(use_, input_ptr_); }
511 bool operator==(const iterator& other) const {
512 return input_ptr_ == other.input_ptr_;
513 }
514 bool operator!=(const iterator& other) const { return !(*this == other); }
515 iterator& operator++() {
516 input_ptr_++;
517 use_--;
518 return *this;
519 }
520 iterator operator++(int);
521 iterator& operator+=(difference_type offset) {
522 input_ptr_ += offset;
523 use_ -= offset;
524 return *this;
525 }
526 iterator operator+(difference_type offset) const {
527 return iterator(use_ - offset, input_ptr_ + offset);
528 }
529 difference_type operator-(const iterator& other) const {
530 return input_ptr_ - other.input_ptr_;
531 }
532
533 private:
534 friend class Node;
535
536 explicit iterator(Use* use, ZoneNodePtr* input_ptr)
537 : use_(use), input_ptr_(input_ptr) {}
538
539 Use* use_;
540 ZoneNodePtr* input_ptr_;
541};

612// A forward iterator to visit the uses edges of a node.
613class Node::UseEdges::iterator final {
614 public:
615 iterator(const iterator& other) = default;
616
617 Edge operator*() const { return Edge(current_, current_->input_ptr()); }
618 bool operator==(const iterator& other) const {
619 return current_ == other.current_;
620 }
621 bool operator!=(const iterator& other) const { return !(*this == other); }
622 iterator& operator++() {
623 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_);
624 current_ = next_;
625 next_ = current_ ? static_cast<Node::Use*>(current_->next) : nullptr;
626 return *this;
627 }
628 iterator operator++(int);
629
630 private:
631 friend class Node::UseEdges;
632
633 iterator() : current_(nullptr), next_(nullptr) {}
634 explicit iterator(Node* node)
635 : current_(node->first_use_),
636 next_(current_ ? static_cast<Node::Use*>(current_->next) : nullptr) {}
637
638 Node::Use* current_;
639 Node::Use* next_;
640};

653// A forward iterator to visit the uses of a node.
654class Node::Uses::const_iterator final {
655 public:
656 using iterator_category = std::forward_iterator_tag;
657 using difference_type = int;
658 using value_type = Node*;
659 using pointer = Node**;
660 using reference = Node*&;
661
662 Node* operator*() const { return current_->from(); }
663 bool operator==(const const_iterator& other) const {
664 return other.current_ == current_;
665 }
666 bool operator!=(const const_iterator& other) const {
667 return other.current_ != current_;
668 }
669 const_iterator& operator++() {
670 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_);
671 // Checking no use gets mutated while iterating through them, a potential
672 // very tricky cause of bug.
673 current_ = current_->next;
674#ifdef DEBUG
675 DCHECK_EQ(current_, next_);
676 next_ = current_ ? current_->next : nullptr;
677#endif
678 return *this;
679 }
680 const_iterator operator++(int);
681
682 private:
683 friend class Node::Uses;
684
685 const_iterator() : current_(nullptr) {}
686 explicit const_iterator(Node* node)
687 : current_(node->first_use_)
688#ifdef DEBUG
689 ,
690 next_(current_ ? current_->next : nullptr)
691#endif
692 {
693 }
694
695 Node::Use* current_;
696#ifdef DEBUG
697 Node::Use* next_;
698#endif
699};
